tweet: @matt_levinson @benjaellis Unfortunately the Nolan stuff is not currently on display and Blue Poles is in the process of a restoration. The National Film and Sound Archive has been stripped of funding. The Chinese Garden is good and I can recommend a decent restaurant.

@matt_levinson Find Them on FB, turn up and ask to meet an ATE Elder, read the protocols and be amazed. Archives and NatFilm and Sound Archive has great stuff got kids! Also the Aboriginal Gallery at the Nat Museum - full of wonders. It’s a great time of year in #CBR!

@matt_levinson Galleries, War Memorial, Mint, Questacon, Old/New PHouses, the zoo is great, Inst of sport,  Telstra Tower Black Mnt, Bot Gardens, Deep Space (it's a bit out of town but worth it if into space) Mus of Aust. Democracy, Nat. Mus of Aust, Nat Film/Sound Archive, Tidbinbilla Nat Res
@matt_levinson The film and sound archive was fun

@matt_levinson Things I remember doing in year 5 about 30 years ago: Parliament house, National Film & Sound Archive, Snow day at Mt Blue Cow, Black Mountain Tower (bought a yo-yo), and there was another museum on Walter Burley Griffin and his plan for the city, also watched the fountain.

@NHM_Science @HistMedLibOx @LSHTMhistory @IMSS_Chicago @IASanatomy Casts like these on show at the National Film and Sound Archive in Canberra- some are from death casts others modelled from images. Notable figures like Darwin, Hunter, Lister and key Australian scientists. https://t.co/phOZ0V4Z5L
Sound exhibition is back! Presenting the first of the five pieces chosen from the open call DIVFUSE Sound Archive No. 2. Free entry. https://t.co/4ZCWBTTwvV

Sound exhibition is on. ‘ghost, machines etc…’ by Felix Taylor is a short suite and visual score for field recordings, reverb and distortion. 1 of the 5 pieces chosen from DIVFUSE Sound Archive - an open call for work based on field recordings. 13 May 4-7pm 14/15 May 2:30-6:30pm https://t.co/m8bXo4OlHQ

@kidsinmuseums https://t.co/DQ5OCjL6H4 `The Other Side of Lennon` London Walk
